\nadvanced Power BI features, leading to a 25% increase in user engagement and satisfaction.\n- Improved Database Performance: Implemented data modeling best practices and optimized\ndatabase queries, enhancing system performance by 40%.\n- Led Training and Support Initiatives: Conducted training sessions and provided ongoing support\nto over 100 end-users, boosting proficiency in Power BI and data-driven decision-making\ncapabilities.\n- Achieved Data Governance Compliance: Ensured compliance with data governance and security\nstandards, safeguarding sensitive information and maintaining data integrity across the\norganization.\n\n===== PAGE 2 =====\n\n\u27a2 Interacting with Project Managers and Leads to get a better understanding of Business Process Working with ETL team to modernize the data from Oracle to share point.\n\u27a2 Understanding different sources and business processes to build Power BI Models\n\u27a2 Developing excellent visualizations using DAX, Row Level securities and bookmarks\n\u27a2 Maintaining the contents in Power BI services by scheduling the reports and Managing access.\n\u27a2 Configured and Managed Power BI Gateway and kept Dashboard and reports up to date.\n\u27a2 Validating the report data and working closely with users to get UAT Sign off.\n\u27a2 Experience in integrating Dashboards and Reports with Power Apps.\nAccess Healthcare, Chennai, Management Trainee \u2013 Business Transformation, (02/2018) - (01/2022)\nTechnology: Power BI, Tableau, Share point, SSMS, Excel\nDomain: Healthcare & Finance\n\u27a2 Data Integration with Salesforce Data, SQL integration and various other data sources.\n\u27a2 Stakeholder Management for Sales rep as well as the Directors (Managing Partners VP Business Leads)\nLeads)\n\u27a2 Developed Reports for business end users using Tableau and Power BI\n\u27a2 Intermediate experience using DAX, MDX and writing complex DAX functions across data models\n\u27a2 Supported Sales targets with cohort analysis, driving up-sell + 40%\n\u27a2 Collaborated in creating a data warehouse contributing to 22% improved data reliability.\n\u27a2 Develop new reports based on user requirement and maintain existing report, fix bugs, ETL\npipeline, DAX Functions and add new metrics or KPI into existing report.\n\u27a2 Implement row-level Security among regional directors and manager in Power BI service.\n\u27a2 Collaborated with the finance team to develop a financial reporting dashboard resulting in a 50% reduction.\nreduction in report development time\n\u27a2 Design and develop ETL workflows and datasets in Alteryx to be used by the BI reporting tool. ETL\nspecific for creating datasets (to be used by Tableau Data Extract for BI)\nAccess Healthcare, Chennai, Client Specialist \u2013 Operations Analyst, (08/2016) - (02/2018)\n\u27a2 Use data analysis and qualitative evaluation to determine root causes of a problem\n\u27a2 Analyze trends to deliver clear and compelling data stories to stakeholders\n\u27a2 Design elegant solutions that favor automation, work prevention, and product\nenhancement over manual workflows\n\u27a2 Seek and consume internal and external client feedback to inform decision making\nand improvement opportunities\n\u27a2 Identify opportunities to expand the value we provide to clients through more or better service(s) using your understanding of customer business problems.\n\u27a2 Master workflow design and analysis through Lean Six Sigma or other operational engineering techniques, considering impact on dependent processes and ensuring continuity of work delivery.\n\u27a2 Identify opportunities to expand the value we provide to clients through more or better service(s) using your understanding of customer business problem.\n\n===== PAGE 3 =====\n\n\u27a2 Analyze the assigned inventory on daily basis to ensure meet the production goal set by management.\nResponsible for Collecting payments from Health insurance on accounts assigned.\nMeeting day to day production and quality based on SLA.\nMentoring newly hired trainees.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nData Visualization: MS Power BI, Tableau\nPower platform: Power Apps & Power Pivot\nDatabase:\nSSMS\nLanguages:\nSQL, DAX & Python\nEDUCATION\nBachelor of Electronic and communication Engineering, (2011),\nThangavelu Engineering college, Chennai"}
